-<Z>GM Reminder: <C>Free agents are not available after week 17.<L.33.1>
-<L.6.1>
-<Z>Last Turn <C> We had lots of hassles with the software which sends out reports. Apologies to those who had to chase them, and <L.31.1>
-for those who got multiple copies - it looks like the new system which we trialled last week is much smoother.<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Reminders <C> A couple of pleas - can everyone make sure orders are submitted on time (it's far from helpful when orders dribble<L.31.1>
-in an hour or so late) and also keep credits topped up (there are some who regularly drop to -1, and rely on results being sent out<L.31.1>
-and then forget). It's a minority who do this stuff, but it'll help me if you don't. Please.<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Fans Growth <C> It's relatively minor but in 2024 rules the growth of fans should be 0.8% (not 1%) plus 0.4% per win. The <L.31.1>
-software has (ever since I've been testing it in late 2023) been based on that, but the website was incorrect. The website is now <L.31.1>
-correct, and the actual software hasn't changed. On average, it means about 0.5 LP less per week across the season.<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Next Few Months <C> Please don't be surprised if a few turns run late at some point over the next few months. Unfortunately my<L.31.1>
-father is unwell, so I'm spending time up and down some motorways, potentially at short notice. Please keep an eye on the latest<L.31.1>
-news of the website, as I will post there if things are delayed (and I am able to do so). However, assume games run on time......<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Gameplan Baseball Changes <C> As mentioned over the last month or so, I've some time looking at some changes to Slapshot, <L.31.1>
-Hoopplan and Gameplan Baseball, to and improve the financial balance of the game, make it somewhat more even and provide you with <L.31.1>
-a few more options and decisions. For Gameplan Baseball I've got a webpage with the changes, which you can find at <L.31.1>
-www.pbmsports.com/baseball2024.htm (note it is case sensitive). These will generally come into play at the start of a new <L.31.1>
-season, but most actually impact at the end of the season. I will review them in the autumn, but don't expect any significant<L.31.1>
-changes until then to allow them to bed in, and with other things (see above) taking my focus. <L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Online Turnsheets <C> Please make sure when you input turns online you get the week/turn number correct (it's on your turnsheet).<L.31.1>
-If you get it wrong, there's a risk the turn gets missed. Please also avoid double submission of turns - if they're within minutes<L.31.1>
-the system will only take the latest set, but if they're spread out both may be input and you'll get charged 0.1 credit.<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Slack <C> There's an independent (i.e. I'm not on it) group on Slack of various players in various games (Gameplan, Raceplan, <L.31.1>
-Baseball, etc) covering things run here (and probably offering hints and advice, which may or may not be accurate). For more<L.31.1>
-information, go to gameplanpbm.slack.com, or for an invite contact Alan Milnes on alan@gameplan.org.uk<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Trial Startups <C> The offer of a free trial startup remains available throughout 2024. If you fancy picking up a new team, or <L.31.1>
-trying a different game, check out the options on www.pbmsports.com and drop me a line<L.31.1>

-<Z>GM Reminder: <C>Free agents are not available after week 17.<L.33.1>
-<L.6.1>
-<Z>Reminders <C> A couple of pleas - can everyone make sure orders are submitted on time (it's far from helpful when orders dribble<L.31.1>
-in an hour or so late) and also keep credits topped up (there are some who regularly drop to -1, and rely on results being sent out<L.31.1>
-and then forget). It's a minority who do this stuff, but it'll help me if you don't. Please.<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Fans Growth <C> It's relatively minor but in 2024 rules the growth of fans should be 0.8% (not 1%) plus 0.4% per win. The <L.31.1>
-software has (ever since I've been testing it in late 2023) been based on that, but the website was incorrect. The website is now <L.31.1>
-correct, and the actual software hasn't changed. On average, it means about 0.5 LP less per week across the season.<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Next Few Months <C> Please don't be surprised if a few turns run late at some point over the next few months. Unfortunately my<L.31.1>
-father is unwell, so I'm spending time up and down some motorways, potentially at short notice. Please keep an eye on the latest<L.31.1>
-news of the website, as I will post there if things are delayed (and I am able to do so). However, assume games run on time......<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Gameplan Baseball Changes <C> As mentioned over the last month or so, I've some time looking at some changes to Slapshot, <L.31.1>
-Hoopplan and Gameplan Baseball, to and improve the financial balance of the game, make it somewhat more even and provide you with <L.31.1>
-a few more options and decisions. For Gameplan Baseball I've got a webpage with the changes, which you can find at <L.31.1>
-www.pbmsports.com/baseball2024.htm (note it is case sensitive). These will generally come into play at the start of a new <L.31.1>
-season, but most actually impact at the end of the season. I will review them in the autumn, but don't expect any significant<L.31.1>
-changes until then to allow them to bed in, and with other things (see above) taking my focus. <L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Online Turnsheets <C> Please make sure when you input turns online you get the week/turn number correct (it's on your turnsheet).<L.31.1>
-If you get it wrong, there's a risk the turn gets missed. Please also avoid double submission of turns - if they're within minutes<L.31.1>
-the system will only take the latest set, but if they're spread out both may be input and you'll get charged 0.1 credit.<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Slack <C> There's an independent (i.e. I'm not on it) group on Slack of various players in various games (Gameplan, Raceplan, <L.31.1>
-Baseball, etc) covering things run here (and probably offering hints and advice, which may or may not be accurate). For more<L.31.1>
-information, go to gameplanpbm.slack.com, or for an invite contact Alan Milnes on alan@gameplan.org.uk<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Trial Startups <C> The offer of a free trial startup remains available throughout 2024. If you fancy picking up a new team, or <L.31.1>
-trying a different game, check out the options on www.pbmsports.com and drop me a line<L.31.1>

-<L.6.1>
-<Z>Reminders <C> A couple of pleas - can everyone make sure orders are submitted on time (it's far from helpful when orders dribble<L.31.1>
-in an hour or so late) and also keep credits topped up (there are some who regularly drop to -1, and rely on results being sent out<L.31.1>
-and then forget). It's a minority who do this stuff, but it'll help me if you don't. Please.<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Next Few Months <C> Please don't be surprised if a few turns run late at some point over the next few months. Unfortunately my<L.31.1>
-father is unwell, so I'm spending time up and down some motorways, potentially at short notice. Please keep an eye on the latest<L.31.1>
-news of the website, as I will post there if things are delayed (and I am able to do so). However, assume games run on time......<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Fans Growth <C> It's relatively minor but in 2024 rules the growth of fans should be 0.8% (not 1%) plus 0.4% per win. The <L.31.1>
-software has (ever since I've been testing it in late 2023) been based on that, but the website was incorrect. The website is now <L.31.1>
-correct, and the actual software hasn't changed. On average, it means about 0.5 LP less per week across the season.<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Gameplan Baseball Changes <C> Most leagues have now moved up to 2024 rules, or are getting close. These changes are to improve <L.31.1>
-the financial balance of the game, make it somewhat more even and provide you with a few more options and decisions. For Gameplan <L.31.1>
-Baseball I've got a webpage with the changes, which you can find at www.pbmsports.com/baseball2024.htm (note it is case sensitive). <L.31.1>
-These will generally come into play at the start of a new season, but most actually impact at the end of the season. I will review <L.31.1>
-them in the autumn, but don't expect any changes until then, and with other things (see above) taking my focus. <L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Online Turnsheets <C> Please make sure when you input turns online you get the week/turn number correct (it's on your turnsheet).<L.31.1>
-If you get it wrong, there's a risk the turn gets missed. Please also avoid double submission of turns - if they're within minutes<L.31.1>
-the system will only take the latest set, but if they're spread out both may be input and you'll get charged 0.1 credit.<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Slack <C> There's an independent (i.e. I'm not on it) group on Slack of various players in various games (Gameplan, Raceplan, <L.31.1>
-Baseball, etc) covering things run here (and probably offering hints and advice, which may or may not be accurate). For more<L.31.1>
-information, go to gameplanpbm.slack.com, or for an invite contact Alan Milnes on alan@gameplan.org.uk<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Trial Startups <C> The offer of a free trial startup remains available throughout 2024. If you fancy picking up a new team, or <L.31.1>
-trying a different game, check out the options on www.pbmsports.com and drop me a line<L.31.1>
-<L.1.1>

-<L.6.1>
-<Z>Reminders <C> A couple of pleas - can everyone make sure orders are submitted on time (it's far from helpful when orders dribble<L.31.1>
-in an hour or so late) and also keep credits topped up (there are some who regularly drop to -1, and rely on results being sent out<L.31.1>
-and then forget). It's a minority who do this stuff, but it'll help me if you don't. Please.<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Next Few Months <C> Please don't be surprised if a few turns run late at some point over the next few months. Unfortunately my<L.31.1>
-father is unwell, so I'm spending time up and down some motorways, potentially at short notice. Please keep an eye on the latest<L.31.1>
-news of the website, as I will post there if things are delayed (and I am able to do so). However, assume games run on time......<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Fans Growth <C> It's relatively minor but in 2024 rules the growth of fans should be 0.8% (not 1%) plus 0.4% per win. The <L.31.1>
-software has (ever since I've been testing it in late 2023) been based on that, but the website was incorrect. The website is now <L.31.1>
-correct, and the actual software hasn't changed. On average, it means about 0.5 LP less per week across the season.<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Gameplan Baseball Changes <C> Most leagues have now moved up to 2024 rules, or are getting close. These changes are to improve <L.31.1>
-the financial balance of the game, make it somewhat more even and provide you with a few more options and decisions. For Gameplan <L.31.1>
-Baseball I've got a webpage with the changes, which you can find at www.pbmsports.com/baseball2024.htm (note it is case sensitive). <L.31.1>
-These will generally come into play at the start of a new season, but most actually impact at the end of the season. I will review <L.31.1>
-them in the autumn, but don't expect any changes until then, and with other things (see above) taking my focus. <L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Online Turnsheets <C> Please make sure when you input turns online you get the week/turn number correct (it's on your turnsheet).<L.31.1>
-If you get it wrong, there's a risk the turn gets missed. Please also avoid double submission of turns - if they're within minutes<L.31.1>
-the system will only take the latest set, but if they're spread out both may be input and you'll get charged 0.1 credit.<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Slack <C> There's an independent (i.e. I'm not on it) group on Slack of various players in various games (Gameplan, Raceplan, <L.31.1>
-Baseball, etc) covering things run here (and probably offering hints and advice, which may or may not be accurate). For more<L.31.1>
-information, go to gameplanpbm.slack.com, or for an invite contact Alan Milnes on alan@gameplan.org.uk<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Trial Startups <C> The offer of a free trial startup remains available throughout 2024. If you fancy picking up a new team, or <L.31.1>
-trying a different game, check out the options on www.pbmsports.com and drop me a line<L.31.1>

-<L.6.1>
-<Z>Reminders <C> A couple of pleas - can everyone make sure orders are submitted on time (it's far from helpful when orders dribble<L.31.1>
-in an hour or so late) and also keep credits topped up (there are some who regularly drop to -1, and rely on results being sent out<L.31.1>
-and then forget). It's a minority who do this stuff, but it'll help me if you don't. Please.<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Next Few Months <C> Please don't be surprised if a few turns run late at some point over the next few months. Unfortunately my<L.31.1>
-father is unwell, so I'm spending time up and down some motorways, potentially at short notice. Please keep an eye on the latest<L.31.1>
-news of the website, as I will post there if things are delayed (and I am able to do so). However, assume games run on time......<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Fans Growth <C> It's relatively minor but in 2024 rules the growth of fans should be 0.8% (not 1%) plus 0.4% per win. The <L.31.1>
-software has (ever since I've been testing it in late 2023) been based on that, but the website was incorrect. The website is now <L.31.1>
-correct, and the actual software hasn't changed. On average, it means about 0.5 LP less per week across the season.<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Gameplan Baseball Changes <C> Most leagues have now moved up to 2024 rules, or are getting close. These changes are to improve <L.31.1>
-the financial balance of the game, make it somewhat more even and provide you with a few more options and decisions. For Gameplan <L.31.1>
-Baseball I've got a webpage with the changes, which you can find at www.pbmsports.com/baseball2024.htm (note it is case sensitive). <L.31.1>
-These will generally come into play at the start of a new season, but most actually impact at the end of the season. I will review <L.31.1>
-them in the autumn, but don't expect any changes until then, and with other things (see above) taking my focus. <L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Online Turnsheets <C> Please make sure when you input turns online you get the week/turn number correct (it's on your turnsheet).<L.31.1>
-If you get it wrong, there's a risk the turn gets missed. Please also avoid double submission of turns - if they're within minutes<L.31.1>
-the system will only take the latest set, but if they're spread out both may be input and you'll get charged 0.1 credit.<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Slack <C> There's an independent (i.e. I'm not on it) group on Slack of various players in various games (Gameplan, Raceplan, <L.31.1>
-Baseball, etc) covering things run here (and probably offering hints and advice, which may or may not be accurate). For more<L.31.1>
-information, go to gameplanpbm.slack.com, or for an invite contact Alan Milnes on alan@gameplan.org.uk<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Trial Startups <C> The offer of a free trial startup remains available throughout 2024. If you fancy picking up a new team, or <L.31.1>
-trying a different game, check out the options on www.pbmsports.com and drop me a line<L.31.1>
-<L.1.1>

-<Z>Gameplan Baseball Changes <C> Most leagues have now moved up to 2024 rules, or are getting close. These changes are to improve <L.31.1>
-the financial balance of the game, make it somewhat more even and provide you with a few more options and decisions. For Gameplan <L.31.1>
-Baseball I've got a webpage with the changes, which you can find at www.pbmsports.com/baseball2024.htm (note it is case sensitive). <L.31.1>
-These will generally come into play at the start of a new season, but most actually impact at the end of the season. I will review <L.31.1>
-them in the autumn, but don't expect any changes until then, and with other things (see above) taking my focus. <L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Online Turnsheets <C> Please make sure when you input turns online you get the week/turn number correct (it's on your turnsheet).<L.31.1>
-If you get it wrong, there's a risk the turn gets missed. Please also avoid double submission of turns - if they're within minutes<L.31.1>
-the system will only take the latest set, but if they're spread out both may be input and you'll get charged 0.1 credit.<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Slack <C> There's an independent (i.e. I'm not on it) group on Slack of various players in various games (Gameplan, Raceplan, <L.31.1>
-Baseball, etc) covering things run here (and probably offering hints and advice, which may or may not be accurate). For more<L.31.1>
-information, go to gameplanpbm.slack.com, or for an invite contact Alan Milnes on alan@gameplan.org.uk<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Trial Startups <C> The offer of a free trial startup remains available throughout 2024. If you fancy picking up a new team, or <L.31.1>
-trying a different game, check out the options on www.pbmsports.com and drop me a line<L.31.1>
-<L.1.1>
-<P>

-<Z>Gameplan Baseball Changes <C> Most leagues have now moved up to 2024 rules, or are getting close. These changes are to improve <L.31.1>
-the financial balance of the game, make it somewhat more even and provide you with a few more options and decisions. For Gameplan <L.31.1>
-Baseball I've got a webpage with the changes, which you can find at www.pbmsports.com/baseball2024.htm (note it is case sensitive). <L.31.1>
-These will generally come into play at the start of a new season, but most actually impact at the end of the season. I will review <L.31.1>
-them in the autumn, but don't expect any changes until then, and with other things (see above) taking my focus. <L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Online Turnsheets <C> Please make sure when you input turns online you get the week/turn number correct (it's on your turnsheet).<L.31.1>
-If you get it wrong, there's a risk the turn gets missed. Please also avoid double submission of turns - if they're within minutes<L.31.1>
-the system will only take the latest set, but if they're spread out both may be input and you'll get charged 0.1 credit.<L.31.1>

-<Z><U>Messages<UC><C><L.36.1>
-<Z>GM Reminder: <C>Free agents are not available after week 17.<L.33.1>
-<L.6.1>
-<Z>Reminders <C> A couple of pleas - can everyone make sure orders are submitted on time (it's far from helpful when orders dribble<L.31.1>
-in an hour or so late) and also keep credits topped up (there are some who regularly drop to -1, and rely on results being sent out<L.31.1>
-and then forget). It's a minority who do this stuff, but it'll help me if you don't. Please.<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Next Few Months <C> Please don't be surprised if a few turns run late at some point over the next few months. Unfortunately my<L.31.1>
-father is unwell, so I'm spending time up and down some motorways, potentially at short notice. Please keep an eye on the latest<L.31.1>
-news of the website, as I will post there if things are delayed (and I am able to do so). However, assume games run on time......<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Fans Growth <C> It's relatively minor but in 2024 rules the growth of fans should be 0.8% (not 1%) plus 0.4% per win. The <L.31.1>
-software has (ever since I've been testing it in late 2023) been based on that, but the website was incorrect. The website is now <L.31.1>
-correct, and the actual software hasn't changed. On average, it means about 0.5 LP less per week across the season.<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Gameplan Baseball Changes <C> Most leagues have now moved up to 2024 rules, or are getting close. These changes are to improve <L.31.1>
-the financial balance of the game, make it somewhat more even and provide you with a few more options and decisions. For Gameplan <L.31.1>
-Baseball I've got a webpage with the changes, which you can find at www.pbmsports.com/baseball2024.htm (note it is case sensitive). <L.31.1>
-These will generally come into play at the start of a new season, but most actually impact at the end of the season. I will review <L.31.1>
-them in the autumn, but don't expect any changes until then, and with other things (see above) taking my focus. <L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Online Turnsheets <C> Please make sure when you input turns online you get the week/turn number correct (it's on your turnsheet).<L.31.1>
-If you get it wrong, there's a risk the turn gets missed. Please also avoid double submission of turns - if they're within minutes<L.31.1>
-the system will only take the latest set, but if they're spread out both may be input and you'll get charged 0.1 credit.<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Slack <C> There's an independent (i.e. I'm not on it) group on Slack of various players in various games (Gameplan, Raceplan, <L.31.1>
-Baseball, etc) covering things run here (and probably offering hints and advice, which may or may not be accurate). For more<L.31.1>
-information, go to gameplanpbm.slack.com, or for an invite contact Alan Milnes on alan@gameplan.org.uk<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Trial Startups <C> The offer of a free trial startup remains available throughout 2024. If you fancy picking up a new team, or <L.31.1>
-trying a different game, check out the options on www.pbmsports.com and drop me a line<L.31.1>

-<Z>GM Reminder: <C>Free agents are not available after week 17.<L.33.1>
-<L.6.1>
-<Z>Reminders <C> A couple of pleas - can everyone make sure orders are submitted on time (it's far from helpful when orders dribble<L.31.1>
-in an hour or so late) and also keep credits topped up (there are some who regularly drop to -1, and rely on results being sent out<L.31.1>
-and then forget). It's a minority who do this stuff, but it'll help me if you don't. Please.<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Next Few Months <C> Please don't be surprised if a few turns run late at some point over the next few months. Unfortunately my<L.31.1>
-father is unwell, so I'm spending time up and down some motorways, potentially at short notice. Please keep an eye on the latest<L.31.1>
-news of the website, as I will post there if things are delayed (and I am able to do so). However, assume games run on time......<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Fans Growth <C> It's relatively minor but in 2024 rules the growth of fans should be 0.8% (not 1%) plus 0.4% per win. The <L.31.1>
-software has (ever since I've been testing it in late 2023) been based on that, but the website was incorrect. The website is now <L.31.1>
-correct, and the actual software hasn't changed. On average, it means about 0.5 LP less per week across the season.<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Gameplan Baseball Changes <C> Most leagues have now moved up to 2024 rules, or are getting close. These changes are to improve <L.31.1>
-the financial balance of the game, make it somewhat more even and provide you with a few more options and decisions. For Gameplan <L.31.1>
-Baseball I've got a webpage with the changes, which you can find at www.pbmsports.com/baseball2024.htm (note it is case sensitive). <L.31.1>
-These will generally come into play at the start of a new season, but most actually impact at the end of the season. I will review <L.31.1>
-them in the autumn, but don't expect any changes until then, and with other things (see above) taking my focus. <L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Online Turnsheets <C> Please make sure when you input turns online you get the week/turn number correct (it's on your turnsheet).<L.31.1>
-If you get it wrong, there's a risk the turn gets missed. Please also avoid double submission of turns - if they're within minutes<L.31.1>
-the system will only take the latest set, but if they're spread out both may be input and you'll get charged 0.1 credit.<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Slack <C> There's an independent (i.e. I'm not on it) group on Slack of various players in various games (Gameplan, Raceplan, <L.31.1>
-Baseball, etc) covering things run here (and probably offering hints and advice, which may or may not be accurate). For more<L.31.1>
-information, go to gameplanpbm.slack.com, or for an invite contact Alan Milnes on alan@gameplan.org.uk<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Trial Startups <C> The offer of a free trial startup remains available throughout 2024. If you fancy picking up a new team, or <L.31.1>
-trying a different game, check out the options on www.pbmsports.com and drop me a line<L.31.1>

-and then forget). It's a minority who do this stuff, but it'll help me if you don't. Please.<L.31.1>

-news of the website, as I will post there if things are delayed (and I am able to do so). However, assume games run on time......<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Gameplan Baseball Changes <C> Most leagues have now moved up to 2024 rules, or are getting close. These changes are to improve <L.31.1>
-the financial balance of the game, make it somewhat more even and provide you with a few more options and decisions. For Gameplan <L.31.1>
-Baseball I've got a webpage with the changes, which you can find at www.pbmsports.com/baseball2024.htm (note it is case sensitive). <L.31.1>
-These will generally come into play at the start of a new season, but most actually impact at the end of the season. I will review <L.31.1>
-them in the autumn, but don't expect any changes until then, and with other things (see above) taking my focus. <L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Online Turnsheets <C> Please make sure when you input turns online you get the week/turn number correct (it's on your turnsheet).<L.31.1>
-If you get it wrong, there's a risk the turn gets missed. Please also avoid double submission of turns - if they're within minutes<L.31.1>
-the system will only take the latest set, but if they're spread out both may be input and you'll get charged 0.1 credit.<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Slack <C> There's an independent (i.e. I'm not on it) group on Slack of various players in various games (Gameplan, Raceplan, <L.31.1>
-Baseball, etc) covering things run here (and probably offering hints and advice, which may or may not be accurate). For more<L.31.1>
-information, go to gameplanpbm.slack.com, or for an invite contact Alan Milnes on alan@gameplan.org.uk<L.31.1>

-Just let me have a team name and I'll set you up in preseason. Nothing to lose by trying it.........<L.31.1>

-<Z>Reminders <C> A couple of pleas - can everyone make sure orders are submitted on time (it's far from helpful when orders dribble<L.31.1>
-in an hour or so late) and also keep credits topped up (there are some who regularly drop to -1, and rely on results being sent out<L.31.1>
-and then forget). It's a minority who do this stuff, but it'll help me if you don't. Please.<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Next Few Months <C> Please don't be surprised if a few turns run late at some point over the next few months. Unfortunately my<L.31.1>
-father is unwell, so I'm spending time up and down some motorways, potentially at short notice. Please keep an eye on the latest<L.31.1>
-news of the website, as I will post there if things are delayed (and I am able to do so). However, assume games run on time......<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Gameplan Baseball Changes <C> Most leagues have now moved up to 2024 rules, or are getting close. These changes are to improve <L.31.1>
-the financial balance of the game, make it somewhat more even and provide you with a few more options and decisions. For Gameplan <L.31.1>
-Baseball I've got a webpage with the changes, which you can find at www.pbmsports.com/baseball2024.htm (note it is case sensitive). <L.31.1>
-These will generally come into play at the start of a new season, but most actually impact at the end of the season. I will review <L.31.1>
-them in the autumn, but don't expect any changes until then, and with other things (see above) taking my focus. <L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Online Turnsheets <C> Please make sure when you input turns online you get the week/turn number correct (it's on your turnsheet).<L.31.1>
-If you get it wrong, there's a risk the turn gets missed. Please also avoid double submission of turns - if they're within minutes<L.31.1>
-the system will only take the latest set, but if they're spread out both may be input and you'll get charged 0.1 credit.<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Slack <C> There's an independent (i.e. I'm not on it) group on Slack of various players in various games (Gameplan, Raceplan, <L.31.1>
-Baseball, etc) covering things run here (and probably offering hints and advice, which may or may not be accurate). For more<L.31.1>
-information, go to gameplanpbm.slack.com, or for an invite contact Alan Milnes on alan@gameplan.org.uk<L.31.1>

-<Z>Reminders <C> A couple of pleas - can everyone make sure orders are submitted on time (it's far from helpful when orders dribble<L.31.1>
-in an hour or so late) and also keep credits topped up (there are some who regularly drop to -1, and rely on results being sent out<L.31.1>
-and then forget). It's a minority who do this stuff, but it'll help me if you don't. Please.<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Next Few Months <C> Please don't be surprised if a few turns run late at some point over the next few months. Unfortunately my<L.31.1>
-father is unwell, so I'm spending time up and down some motorways, potentially at short notice. Please keep an eye on the latest<L.31.1>
-news of the website, as I will post there if things are delayed (and I am able to do so). However, assume games run on time......<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Gameplan Baseball Changes <C> Most leagues have now moved up to 2024 rules, or are getting close. These changes are to improve <L.31.1>
-the financial balance of the game, make it somewhat more even and provide you with a few more options and decisions. For Gameplan <L.31.1>
-Baseball I've got a webpage with the changes, which you can find at www.pbmsports.com/baseball2024.htm (note it is case sensitive). <L.31.1>
-These will generally come into play at the start of a new season, but most actually impact at the end of the season. I will review <L.31.1>
-them in the autumn, but don't expect any changes until then, and with other things (see above) taking my focus. <L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Online Turnsheets <C> Please make sure when you input turns online you get the week/turn number correct (it's on your turnsheet).<L.31.1>
-If you get it wrong, there's a risk the turn gets missed. Please also avoid double submission of turns - if they're within minutes<L.31.1>
-the system will only take the latest set, but if they're spread out both may be input and you'll get charged 0.1 credit.<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Slack <C> There's an independent (i.e. I'm not on it) group on Slack of various players in various games (Gameplan, Raceplan, <L.31.1>
-Baseball, etc) covering things run here (and probably offering hints and advice, which may or may not be accurate). For more<L.31.1>
-information, go to gameplanpbm.slack.com, or for an invite contact Alan Milnes on alan@gameplan.org.uk<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Trial Startups <C> The offer of a free trial startup remains available throughout 2024. If you fancy picking up a new team, or <L.31.1>
-trying a different game, check out the options on www.pbmsports.com and drop me a line<L.31.1>

-the system will only take the latest set, but if they're spread out both may be input and you'll get charged 0.1 credit.<L.31.1>

-away (fifteen of them over the summer) will be a thing of the past as my father passed away in August.<L.31.1>

-<Z>Online Turnsheets <C> Please make sure when you input turns online you get the week/turn number correct (it's on your turnsheet).<L.31.1>
-If you get it wrong, there's a risk the turn gets missed. Please also avoid double submission of turns - if they're within minutes<L.31.1>
-the system will only take the latest set, but if they're spread out both may be input and you'll get charged 0.1 credit.<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Slack <C> There's an independent (i.e. I'm not on it) group on Slack of various players in various games (Gameplan, Raceplan, <L.31.1>
-Baseball, etc) covering things run here (and probably offering hints and advice, which may or may not be accurate). For more<L.31.1>
-information, go to gameplanpbm.slack.com, or for an invite contact Alan Milnes on alan@gameplan.org.uk<L.31.1>
-<L.12.1>
-<Z>Trial Startups <C> The offer of a free trial startup remains available throughout 2024. If you fancy picking up a new team, or <L.31.1>
-trying a different game, check out the options on www.pbmsports.com and drop me a line<L.31.1>
